For context, the restaurant closes at 4pm on Sundays. We paid (with the hostess by the way because Valerie did not come get our debit card) and were out of the doors at 4:05pm.

This was our first time visiting Dame's Chicken and Waffles in Cary and was extremely disappointed in the service and behavior of Valerie. Unfortunately, I will not be returning to this location and spending time and money in an establishment that condones this kind of behavior.

Dames Chicken and Waffles corporate office, restaurant management, and/or God himself should have a conversation with Valerie and I pray she has the day she deserves.

title: Dame's Chicken & Waffles
text:
A Friendly Visit to Dames Chicken and Waffles

I had been eagerly anticipating my first visit to Dames Chicken and Waffles, so I arrived bright and early on a Sunday morning at 9:45 am, only to realize that they don't open until 10 am ‚Äì my bad for not double-checking the hours beforehand! But arriving early turned out to be a blessing, as a small line had already formed outside, and more folks were joining in anticipation of a delicious breakfast.

Once seated, I ordered a glass of water, coffee, and orange juice. However, my excitement dipped momentarily when I noticed some food crumbs in my water. Nonetheless, I decided to give the menu a good look, settling on a waffle with maple pecan-infused butter and the American breakfast.

The waffle, accompanied by its unique buttery topping, was decent, but not quite the flavor explosion I had hoped for. The American breakfast, unfortunately, didn't quite hit the mark either ‚Äì the turkey bacon was a tad bland, and the sausage patties seemed a bit overdone. But hey, the buttery grits were surprisingly tasty!

To my disappointment, the coffee arrived on the colder side and lacked the robust flavor I was expecting. Despite these minor setbacks, when the bill arrived, I couldn't help but feel it was a tad steep for the overall dining experience.

In the end, while my visit to Dames Chicken and Waffles didn't entirely live up to my expectations, I left with a hopeful outlook. I'm confident that with a bit of attention to cleanliness and perhaps some tweaks to the menu, this charming spot has the potential to provide an even more delightful dining experience for its future guests.

There is a large patio with a projector for only the best games. Large yard games for everyone to enjoy. TV‚Äôs everywhere so you never miss a game or Chive TV lol. title: Herons
text: WOW. Just wow. I should start by saying I am very picky. I am a chicken tender and california roll kind of girl. The courses I chose were the crab, scallop, duck, and chocolate. The crab was EXQUISITE. Who knew sea urchin custard would actually be good? The scallop was cooked to perfection, the duck was the perfect cut, and the passionfruit and chocolate combo was to die for. The small bites in between were amazing too- wonderful breads and the best corn dogs you could ask for! The service was amazing as well. Our fabulous server Casey explained everything in great detail and made sure we were well taken care of. The presentation of food and drink as well as the clearing of plates were so smooth and clearly well practiced. Each staff member I interacted with was full of knowledge and so amazing helping! Megan made the best hot chocolates, Carlos followed up with perfectly foamed and decorated lattes. Kacy, Rachel, Lizzie, Mari, Josie, Mike, and Tim were fantastic about clearing exactly on time and so incredibly kind in my brief interactions with them. Kalyn was a fantastic hostess and so incredibly accommodating. Another fantastic part of the evening was meeting the wonderful Chef Spencer! He and all of the other kitchen staff put SO much care and effort into making our dishes wonderful. The atmosphere was very cozy with lovely music playing just quiet enough for conversation but just loud enough to set an uplifting mood. I‚Äôm sure there are many other names I forgot to get, but truly the experience was wonderful and one I will never forget. Thank you to the amazing Heron‚Äôs staff for making my birthday so special! If you‚Äôre looking for a place to have the *perfect* fine-dining experience, Herons is definitely the way to go.

title: Herons
text:
We were lucky enough to have our anniversary celebration dinner at Herons last night. OMG, what an outstanding experience! As others have stated, the service was impeccable yet very personable and down to earth. And that statement applies to everyone with whom we came into contact.

The place was beautifully decorated but not the least bit overbearing. And the atmosphere was quiet yet celebratory throughout the restaurant. Clearly everyone there was happy.

And for the food.... I can't begin to describe the complexity of flavors. Every course was unique and delightful. We chose the wine pairing option; it was every bit as delicious and harmonious as the food creations. The Sommelier knew his trade, providing outstanding selections that complimented every course.

We're so happy to have chosen Herons for our celebration.

title: Herons
text: We went for the valentine's day dinner and had an incredible time. Definitely very pricey but the whole experience was worth it. We had a continuous stream of very interesting, beautiful and delicious dishes for almost three hours. title: Ruth's Chris Steak House
text: Each time we've been to Ruth's Chris it was been a fabulous experience. The service is amazing. Friendly, prompt and knowledgeable, not to mention the food comes out very quick. The atmosphere is always calm, quiet and intimate. The food is outstanding- not a single complaint. We've had the porterhouse for two, ribeyes, garlic mash, creamed spinach, lyonnaise, osso bucco ravioli and banana foster. Everything was amazing and piping hot. title: Ruth's Chris Steak House
text:
We have been long time customers of this location. We even hold our annual company Christmas parties at Ruth's. However, last night we wanted to have a nice meal, but had a time limitation, due to friend leaving on a flight. We decided to get our meal "to go" so that we had some schedule control. We ordered on 4-11-24 at 4:30 pm online with a 6:30 pick up. When we arrived no one new anything about our order. The server at the bar was extremely friendly, apologetic and was helpful, but returned without the order. We showed the receipt and she agreed that all was in order. The server said they would get "right on it" and  would have our order soon. At nearly 7, she brought out the order.
On the way out, we asked to speak to the manager. Surprisingly, he was aware of the situation, but did not seek us out. Whether intentional or not, he came across as aloof and unconcerned. He said that there was little he could do since we had paid for the meal online. He said that they didn't know their "tablet" wasn't working and they didn't receive the order, so.......

In an upscale dining establishment like Ruth's and particularly since we have been long time customers, we would anticipate a better experience. Frankly, we would have rated the service 0-1 if not for the server that helped us at the bar.

Sadly, based on this experience, we will take our business elsewhere.

title: Ruth's Chris Steak House
text:
The quality of food at Ruth Chris has gone down. My ribeye  had no flavor. The only part that was good was the fat. I have eaten at Ruth Chris a few times and this was my husband first time. He said we won't be going back. His red snapper looked like a baby tilapia and he said it was distasteful along with the bed of rice. We did like our calamari appetizer and the creamed spinach was good. Also, my wine was good (Vietti). If we try Ruth Chris again it will be in North Hills. This one was a huge disappointment when I was craving a flavorful steak.

Our server was good and attentive. There were two managers that walked around checking on guests and seemed engaged, however, one of them was selective in who he approached. We were in a more private area and he consistently went to the other two tables but didn't ever come to my husband and I table. He should be careful with behavior like that. It could be perceived negatively.

title: Ruth's Chris Steak House
text:
I‚Äôm not even a picky eater (and I was very hungry) so I‚Äôd have eaten even a mediocre meal and enjoyed it at that point - but I still had to send back a few items.

The calamari tasted like soggy batter, probably the worst calamari I‚Äôve had.

My steak had far too much butter. It was drowning in it to where the steak tasted awful.

When I mentioned to the manger they just argued with me and then picked it up and walked off.

I didn‚Äôt know if they were making a new one, or refunding me and not bringing a new one, or what - until server explained what the plan was.

I don‚Äôt want to only point out negatives always try to be balanced - our server was nice and honest, the wine was quite good, and so was the desert.

That said, for what it costs they really do need to work on how they prepare some dishes to be more consistent- and they need a manager who can communicate effectively or arms who actually cares about having standards.

As many have noted in the last 9-12 months of reviews the place has gone downhill.

title: Hong Kong No. 1
text:
I have been going to this takeout restaurant for over ten years now and I could not say enough good things about it. I get to enjoy the delicious flavors of Chinese food right from my own home. From the moment I opened my shrimp lo mien and sesame chicken, I was impressed by the inviting aromas that wafted from each dish.
The menu offered an extensive selection of classic Chinese dishes, ranging from General Tso's chicken to vegetable lo mein. Each item I ordered was bursting with flavor and cooked to perfection. The attention to detail in preparation was evident, with ingredients and a balance of flavors that made every bite a delightful experience.
The efficiency of the take-out service was commendable. My order was ready for pickup within the promised time, and the staff was friendly and accommodating.
Portion sizes were generous, ensuring that I had enough for a satisfying meal and leftovers for the next day. This value for money made the experience even more enjoyable.
Chinese take-out restaurants often serve as a convenient and reliable option, and this particular establishment did not disappoint. It delivered a delicious and hassle-free dining experience, making it an ideal choice for those looking to savor the flavors of Chinese cuisine without the need for a sit-down meal.

title: Sophie's Grill And Bar
text:
My boyfriend and I dined here a few weeks ago for a date night and we were very impressed. We were both craving Eastern European food and Sophie's exceeded our expectations. The owner is from Bulgaria and has a lot of unique food and drinks on her menu.

We were able to make reservations and we asked for a booth. There are lots of fresh flowers and plants decorating this restaurant. We loved the vibes and definitely felt like we were transported to a restaurant in Europe. I started with a bourbon drink called the Boulevardier with Campari and it was delicious. My boyfriend had a bourbon. We ordered the Armenian figs appetizer, and my only complaint is the bacon was barely cooked. That is on me though because I should have specified we like our bacon well done.

For our entrees my boyfriend had the Balkan's wine kebab and I had the stuffed cabbage rolls. My entree was really good, but next time I'm ordering the wine kebab. The flavors were amazing! It consisted of slow roasted chicken, veggies and rice. The bartender was our server and she was wonderful. We both can't wait to return.

I've been coming to this place now and then since they opened this restaurant because it's close to my house. This is not the one of best szechuan restaurants although I have not found one in NC yet like ones in CA or NY. However, better than or similar to szechuan garden or chengdu 7 in my opinion.

I only had limited number of dishes so far, but here are what I recommend and not recommend:

Not recommend
- General Tso's chicken, it is not typical general tso dish. They use ketchup or tomato based sauce and not spicy at all. Also wish they cut the meat into smaller pieces.

- Kungpao chicken, same reason above

- Beef string bean with garlic sauce, expected clean garlic based sauce, but it had the same flavor of General Tso. Disappointed.

- Lo Mein or Chow Fun, any noodle based dish, they way overcook noodles, so noodles become too mushy and stuck together (see photo)

- Any fried rice, just not good.

- Mushu (Pork) - Super sweet and very little meat, mostly cabbage, wish they use shredded fresh cooked pork, not precooked dry bbq pork (see photo)

Recommend
- Chongqing diced chicken, not the best I've had but pretty good, it is fried (see photo)

- Salt and pepper spare rib, good but it is also fried (see photo)

I will update my review if I try new dishes.

text:
Take some pride. Terrible leadership. $140 order for take out and once I arrive (after the recommended 25min wait time) we got to wait another 40min for our food. That led to a cold pizza that we sent back which then led to cold food. The host group up front was doing their best as they tried to handle a ton of people and demands and had an average age of 14 ha! So I don‚Äôt blame them. But the owner standing in the back, on his phone several times, walking around like everything was fine was clearly the issue.
Your people are drowning. Now is not the time to act like everything is okay. Jump in and be a soldier. Rescue the drowning and take some pride in your establishment. Your employees are looking to you for guidance and help‚Ä¶ unfortunately you were no where around them.
Been here several times. The food isn‚Äôt bad and the vibe is fine. But I can‚Äôt watch these poor kids treading water while you think everything is good.
Won‚Äôt be back but I doubt that matters. If it did, you would have been at the front with the other 15 or so people who were frustrated at their order, wait time, service, and experience.

title: La Cocina Mexican Restaurant Cary
text: My husband and I came to North Carolina from Pennsylvania for a friend's wedding. Our hotel was near and my husband decided to surprise me with lunch. I had no idea where we were going, we just knew we were starving. To my absolute delight he brings me here to La Cocina!!! This establishment has such a cozy, relaxed atmosphere and I loved that they were playing good old fashioned Spanish music that I was super familiar with and was able to sing along with and dance in my seat to, as I enjoyed my meal. There was a very small "lunch crowd" I guess you could call it but, not rowdy or anything of the sort thankfully. Now to the SERVICE! Our server was Alex (Alejandro actually but I guess he uses Alex for the job). This gentleman is an absolute GEM!!! From the moment he introduced himself and took our drink orders, his demeanor was wonderful. He gave awesome, detailed recommendations about the variety of sangria's and drinks that they served. I went with his recommendations! lol When he brought us our drinks, he asked if we were ready to order and I proceeded to ask him about the menu since it was my first time ever visiting. He was so detailed and took his time explaining as well as recommending a variety of items to try. My husband ordered the Tender Ribeye and I ordered the Shrimp Fajitas. They served you tortilla chips and homemade salsa as you wait for your food. Without a doubt, their house salsa is one of, if not THE best salsa both my husband and I have ever had! We told Alex how much we enjoyed it and I didn't realize it at the time but, he took note of it! (keep this in mind for later). Now, my mother back in Pa has been looking for a place that makes authentic tamales and unfortunately, we can't find anywhere back home in PA. As luck would have it, what happened to be on the menu???? You guessed it...TAMALES! lol So I told Alex about my mom's predicament with her sooooo desired tamales and told him that I would like to try one to see if I liked it, so as to bring some back to my mom. He jotted down an order for 1 along with the rest of our food and went away to the kitchen. When he comes back, this wonderful gentleman came back with not 1 but 2 tamales, each made differently, so that I may try them and decide which one to take back home. He was super attentive, truly cared about whether or not we were enjoying the food and that we had everything that we needed as well as talking with us as if we were old friends catching up after a long time. All that along with never missing a beat with his other tables! Needless to say my husband and I enjoyed our experience here in every aspect. I ended up ordering a dozen tamales to take back home lol. I thanked Alex for absolutely everything and especially for making my first ever Mexican restaurant experience in North Carolina such a wonderful one. OH, and we also took a huge container of that delicious salsa of theirs back home too! LOL! If you want a great dining experience that will make your taste buds dance, and an even more awesome dining experience because of such amazing quality servers, then definitely come here to La Cocina! My husband and I cannot wait to come back on vacation next year and eat here again!

title: Subway
text: I would have to say I had a great experience the young man who took my order washed his hands when he came out the back and then out gloves on and I appreciate that.  However,  when the older gentleman came from behind he just put gloves on without washing his hands.  I appreciated him making sandwich. text: Saw that they make NY style pizza.  Amazing and just like home.  Found our new favorite place in NC.

text:
Salvio's has incredibly delicious food and their service is excellent.  My mom has sent me surprise pizzas at the pharmacy and they write a note from her on the inside of the box.  They deliver it with a smile because they know it's a surprise and I'll probably cry.
Anna delivered mine today and it was delicious as usual.

title: Salvio's Pizzeria
text: Eat here often - excellent food and service.

title: Salvio's Pizzeria
text: Cleanest pizza spot around! And the steak sub is insanely good. Super friendly service and the pizza is so great

title: Salvio's Pizzeria
text:
After ordering a pizza and salad for delivery, the confirmation indicated 45 minutes. Hey, I'm being lazy so I can deal with the time. However, well before 45 minutes, at my door stood a sweet, smiling delivery person, Anna. She took a moment to connect with me and made my day.
The next delightful/delicious moment was the joy of eating my delicious pizza and salad. The pizza always has generous toppings and I love the crust. It's perfection! Salvio's house salad is also not what most restaurants offer as a "house" salad. Their house salad is packed with tomatoes, banana peppers, black olives, onions etc. Salvio's always takes their food to the next level of deliciousness.

title: Salvio's Pizzeria
text:
Salvio's Cary is the best place for a slice!  Or a salad!  Or a sub!
We get lunch for work at least once a week; from a single person to a large meeting, the food is always fantastic and everyone is raving!  The people are always nice and helpful.  We appreciate you, Salvios!
